## Credentials & Professional Context

This repository hosts a portfolio of certifications and educational history tracking a dual specialization: extensive field expertise in municipal critical infrastructure operations alongside technical training in Information Technology (IT) and Operational Technology (OT/ICS) cybersecurity.

* **23 Years of Core Utility Operations:** Practical, field-tested experience as a lead licensed water and wastewater operator. This background provides a deep understanding of physical process controls, plant logistics, and the real-world operational constraints that dictate industrial security requirements.
* **324 Hours of Verifiable Technical Training:** A multi-decade track record of engineering, calculation, chemistry, and safety coursework certified by the Texas Commission on Environmental Quality (TCEQ).
* **Targeted Cybersecurity Stacking:** Formal validation via industry-standard baselines (CompTIA Security+, ISC2 Certified in Cybersecurity) combined with mission-critical training from the Cybersecurity and Infrastructure Security Agency (CISA) and TEEX.

A complete course-by-course breakdown and digital certificate index is available in the [`00-certifications/README.md`](./00-certifications/README.md) directory.
